  "prompt": "Luis Von Ahn: What is the current business model of Duolingo?",
  "response": "Luis von Ahn's Duolingo primarily operates on a freemium business model with multiple revenue streams:\n\n1. Freemium Model\n- Basic language learning features are free\n- Premium subscription (Duolingo Plus) offers additional features like ad-removal, offline access, and unlimited mistakes\n\n2. Advertising\n- Free users see advertisements within the app\n- Generates revenue through mobile and web ad placements\n\n3. Duolingo English Test\n- A standardized online English proficiency test used by universities and employers\n- Generates significant revenue through test-taking fees\n\n4. Partnerships\n- Collaborations with educational institutions and corporations\n- Potential licensing of language learning technology\n\n5. In-App Purchases\n- Optional virtual currency and additional learning features\n\nThe core strategy remains providing free, accessible language learning while monetizing through premium features, advertisements, and specialized testing services. This approach has helped Duolingo become one of the most popular language learning platforms globally, with millions of active users.\n\nIn 2021, Duolingo went public (NASDAQ: DUOL), further validating its business model and growth potential in the ed-tech market.",
